\">toNNReal</a></span>)</span>)</span></span>)</span>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/Log/Basic.html#Real.log\">Real.log</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Real.exp\">Real.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Neg.neg\">-</a><span class=\"fn\">β</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓒</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Basic.html#CanonicalEnsemble.energy\">energy</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓒</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Basic.html#CanonicalEnsemble.μ\">μ</a></span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓒</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Basic.html#CanonicalEnsemble.dof\">dof</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/SpecialFunctions/Log/Basic.html#Real.log\">Real.log</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓒</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Basic.html#CanonicalEnsemble.phaseSpaceunit\">phaseSpaceunit</a></span></span>)</span>\n  <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Defs.html#Set.Ioi\">Set.Ioi</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Helper: equality (on `Set.Ioi 0`) between the β–parametrized logarithm of the\nphysical partition function and the β–parametrized logarithm of the *mathematical*\npartition function up to the (β–independent) semiclassical correction. This is used only\nto identify derivatives (the correction drops).\nWe add the hypothesis `h_fin` giving finiteness of the Boltzmann measure for every β > 0\n(as needed to ensure the mathematical partition function is strictly positive). ","docLink":"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Lemmas.html#CanonicalEnsemble.log_phys_eq_log_math_sub_const_on_Ioi","kind":"theorem","line":576,"name":"CanonicalEnsemble.log_phys_eq_log_math_sub_const_on_Ioi","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L576-L631"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Lemmas.html#CanonicalEnsemble.meanEnergy_eq_neg_deriv_log_mathZ_of_beta\"><span class=\"name\">CanonicalEnsemble</span>.<span class=\"name\">meanEnergy_eq_neg_deriv_log_mathZ_of_beta</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓒</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/StatisticalMechanics/CanonicalEnsemble/Basic.html#CanonicalEnsemble\">CanonicalEnsemble</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/Thermodynamics/Temperature/Basic.html#Temperature\">Temperature</a>)</span></span